	    <h1>Welcome - Heroku Waza Zen Table</h1>
    <p>The Zen Table is an unique mash-up of art and technology. Imagine the spirits of a zen garden coming alive and dutifully working at your command.
	Inventor <a href="http://twitter.com/fnbrit" target="_blank">Simon Hallam</a> put the <a href="http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/fnbrit/zen-table" target="_blank">traditional zen sand garden into a desktop or coffee-table</a> and then made it work automatically.</p>
	<blockquote>
		Zen-Table is an ingenious mechanism consisting of a microcontroller, strong neodynium magnets and a plotter like mechanism to move the "drawing head" across sand on top of a coffee- or desktop-table. Of course the table is programmable. It allows for static images from a SD-card to be drawn in the sand and also dynamic renderings via an USB-port.
	</blockquote>
	<p>In the Neo4j lounge you find an installment of two tables, idly drawing patterns in the sand when no one watches. But able to respond to the trace of your fingertip or wits of your mind.</p>
	<img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-bsaqXwHW8vY/UHl5rGNbiVI/AAAAAAAAAFI/iZvFz0VGGC8/s400/zen-table-desktop.png"></img>
	<h4>Drawing on the table</h4>
	<p>Put your own mark onto the Zen Table by <a href="/draw">drawing lines on your computer or mobile device.</a>
	As multiple people want to draw at the same time, you'll be given a token that is claimed as soon as there is a free spot. Each session lasts about 3 minutes.
	</p>
